headlines.description: — Kemba Walker made two late free throws and scored a season-high 32 points to help the Boston Celtics snap a three-game losing streak with a 118-112 win over the Indiana Pacers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker's season-high 32 lifts Celtics over Pacers 118-112

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 27 points and the Sacramento Kings snapped a nine-game losing streak with a 110-107 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings snap skid, top Pistons 110-107 in strange finish

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler and the Miami Heat got their most significant win of the season and took down the team with the NBA’s best record in the process.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler, Dragic carry Heat past NBA-best Jazz, 124-116

headlines.description: — Devin Booker and Deandre Ayton each scored 22 points and the Phoenix Suns rallied to beat the Chicago Bulls 106-97, on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker, Deandre Ayton help Suns rally to beat Bulls

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 30 points, Lou Williams added 17 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 119-99 on Friday night to split a two-game series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard has 30 points, Clippers beat Grizzlies for split

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 24 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Atlanta Hawks 118-109 on Friday night after changing uniforms at halftime because a mix-up left the teams wearing similar colors at the start.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shades of red: Thunder beat Hawks after uniform mix-up

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Draymond Green vowed to make up for losing his cool and costing Golden State a win at Charlotte last weekend.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green notches triple-double, Warriors avenge loss to Hornets

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 28 points, Dennis Schröder added 22 in his return to the Lakers' lineup, and Los Angeles snapped its four-game losing streak with a 102-93 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schröder returns, Lakers beat Blazers 102-93 to snap skid
